
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `loadkeys` baraye ta'yin ya tagheer dadane layout keyboard dar Linux estefade mishavad. Ba in dastoor, mitoonid character map-haye mokhtalef ro baraye keyboard-etoon load konid, mesle layout-haye zaban-haye mokhtalef ya character-haye khas.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `loadkeys <filename>` --> ⌨️ Load kardane layout keyboard az yek file.
    🔹 `loadkeys -m <mapfile> <filename>` --> 🗺️ Load kardane yek keymap ba estefade az file mapfile.
    🔹 `loadkeys -d` --> ↩️ Load kardane default keyboard map.
    🔹 `loadkeys -C console` --> 🖥️ Ta'yin kardane console-i ke keymap ro bayad roosh load kard.

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ loadkeys fa

    🔹 Load kardane layout keyboard Farsi (agar file "fa" mojood bashad).

    $ loadkeys /usr/share/keymaps/i386/qwerty/uk.map.gz

    🔹 Load kardane layout keyboard British az file zakhire shode.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ loadkeys us
    
    🔹 Keyboard layout ra be halate default US barmigardanad, agar file `us` dar masir haye standart mojood bashad.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `loadkeys` command is used to load or change the keyboard layout in Linux. You can load different character maps for your keyboard, such as layouts for different languages or special characters.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `loadkeys <filename>` --> ⌨️ Load keyboard layout from a file.
    🔹 `loadkeys -m <mapfile> <filename>` --> 🗺️ Load a keymap using a mapfile.
    🔹 `loadkeys -d` --> ↩️ Load the default keyboard map.
    🔹 `loadkeys -C console` --> 🖥️ Specify the console to load the keymap on.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ loadkeys fa

    🔹 Load the Farsi keyboard layout (if the "fa" file exists).

    $ loadkeys /usr/share/keymaps/i386/qwerty/uk.map.gz

    🔹 Load the British keyboard layout from a stored file.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ loadkeys us

    🔹 Restores the keyboard layout to the default US layout, if the `us` file exists in the standard paths.
